Explanation:

We use a for loop to iterate from 0 to n-1, and calculate the number of people aware of the secret on day n. We add up the number of people who share the secret on each day (delay + forget - i) and take the remainder when divided by delay. This ensures that we only count the number of people who share the secret on each day. Finally, we return the result modulo 1000000007 (prime number 1000000007) to ensure the result fits within the given constraints.

